Zambia have struggled since winning the 2012 African Cup. 

The team drew all three of its group matches at the 2013 tournament and was eliminated. This year, they have taken the lead in both matches, but they drew 1-1 with Congo in their opening match before losing on Thursday.

Tunisia will play its final group match against Congo on Monday in Bata, while Zambia will take on Cape Verde in Ebebiyin.

 

 

 

